    {
      "id": "e2854540_2bb149bc",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/components/policy-pap/resources/config/papParameters.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 118,
      "message": "Question: This looks like spring kafka configuration. So, for spring boot apps, are we going to use Spring Kafka client, and for non spring apps like PDPs only we are going for policy-common implementation (using kafka java client library).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2022-07-06 14:49:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "aeb10d22_06f6a19b",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 220,
      "message": "Question: Are these topic names case sensitive? I think today, these are full upper case.\n\nAlso, I think the main challenge when moving to strimzi is the creation of topics. Unlike DMaaP topics will not be created automatically when an event is published. Depending on use cases, creating topics as per policies running in PDPs will have to be more of a downstream task. Still, I think it is better to have some standard topics like \"unauthenticated.DCAE_CL_OUTPUT\", \"POLICY-CL-MGT\" etc that are used by standard usecases (or atleast for testing purposes) created by default.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2022-07-06 14:49:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
